North White traveled to Rossville today. The Vikings were able to secure a victory against the Hornets 4-0. Scoring for North White were Julian Gomez, Kevin Garcia, Auner Ramirez, and Andie Menjivar with one goal apiece. September 5 at 6:18 PM ¬∑

North White Cross Country
September 5 at 3:23 PM ¬∑

GREAT DAY OF RUNNING AT CASTON INVITATIONAL!

Of 16 teams and 8 finishers, NW Varsity girls both had season PRs!
Hannah Cosgray earning medal (15th=23:00.21 Season PR)
Olivia Allen (35th=24:48 season PR)

Of 19 teams, NW Boys finished 7th! (missing Jesus) Of 90 finishers:
Dominick Hernandez earning medal (5th= 18:00 Season PR)
Juan Mata Pecina earning medal (9th= 18:30)
Dane Hood (38th= 20:24)
Eli Stearns (58th= 21:47)
Kevin Dahlenburg(85th= 26:15, first race!!)

Of 16 teams, our middle school ladies placed 9th! Of 89 finishers:
Sable George earning medal (6th=12:37 Season PR)
Katy Westerhouse (46th=15:51 PR!)
Gracie Stinson (52nd=16:02)
Mady Westerhouse (65th= 17:04)
Destiny Spears (69th= 17:25)
Katerin Aldana Cortez (87th= 20:27; 1st meet!)
Of 18 teams, our middle school boys placed 12th! Of 102 finishers:
Liam Kyle (45th= 13:37)
Braylon Sipkema (49th= 13:50)
Blayn Duncan (66th= 14:25)
Brad Pronger (81st= 15:56 PR!)
James Casey (96th= 18:37- 1st meet!)
Zach Watts (101st=22:47 MAJOR PR)
Charlie Williams (102nd=22:48 MAJOR PR

The NW Lady Vikings Soccer team traveled to Covington on Thursday to take on the Lady Trojans in a JV contest. The halftime score had the Vikings down 3-1. Scoring for the Vikings was Reyna Serrano, who shot a perfect penalty kick. Two scores for the Trojans were by penalty kicks. The final score saw the Lady Vikings falling by a final score of 6-1. Vana Leon had 5 saves in the first half while Mackenzie Smolek had 2 saves in the second half.

If you are attending tonight's (9/4) varsity football game at Winamac, please be aware of these procedures.

1. NO TICKETS WILL BE SOLD AT THE GATE

2. Visiting fans will have their own restrooms located in the elementary gym next to the visitor's bleachers.

3. Visiting fans will have the east side of the concession stand and the home team will have the west side of the concession stand.

4. After the game will dismiss the visiting fans 1st, then the home team fans. All fans will leave the facility immediately upon dismissal.

5. Parents wanting to meet the player after the game will do so outside of their locker room. Remember the visiting team will dress across the street in our middle school locker room this year.

6. No pass outs. Once a fan leaves, they will not be allowed back in.

7. Masks/face coverings are required to enter our facilities and fans are encouraged to social distance themselves during the game.

REMINDER: From Mr. Woodcock:

On Thursday, September 3rd, we host Caston in 7 & 8 volleyball, with the 7th grade starting at 6:00 p.m. and 8th grade to follow. Due to COVID concerns with limited seating in our auxiliary gym, We are asking for 7th-grade spectators to leave immediately after the 7th grade contest. I am also requesting that 8th grade spectators not enter the gym until 6:30 p.m. so we don't have to put any restrictions on the number of spectators attending.

Also, Our COVID policies for indoor athletic events:

* Masks are to be worn by all spectators entering the building.

* Masks are to be worn when walking around in the building and when social distancing cannot be maintained.

* You may remove your mask if you are sitting and properly maintaining social distance from other families.

I grew up on my family‚Äôs grain farm in rural Southern Indiana. I was a 4 year FFA member and a 10 year 4-H member. I graduated from Purdue University in 2019 with a major in Agricultural Education and a minor in Crop Sciences.

In my short time as an Agriculture Educator & FFA Advsior I have coached & co-coached multiple state and national FFA teams. I am excited to share my passion for Agriculture with the students and the community of North White! üíôüíõ

-Kari Hoenert

post_text:
From Coach Boszor:

North White hosted cross-county rival Twin Lakes in the first ever meeting of the two teams. It was back and forth early with neither team getting the advantage until Auner Ramirez broke open the scoring and North White never looked back. The Vikings took the win 8-0. Ramirez finished with 1 more goal, but couldn't keep up with teammate Andie Menjivar who scored three on the evening. Ethan Sparks had three assists and Diego Maravilla had ten saves in the shutout victory.

North White will host Morgan Township on Friday at 5:45.

post_text:
From Mr. Woodcock, Athletic Director:

In an effort to help maintain the health and safety of everyone, the Fitness Center will remain closed to the public until at least January 1, 2021.

In January, we will reevaluate the situation and make a decision when to officially reopen. Anyone who has a membership, we will honor your months left on your membership, since the Fitness Center closed in March.

If you wish to be reimbursed for the time you had left on your membership since the closing in March, please contact the Athletic Department and we will accommodate your request.

We apologize for the inconvenience and hope you understand our situation.

post_text:
Hello NW Families:

The teachers and staff at North White miss their students tremendously. It has been too long since they saw all of your smiling faces. So on Friday the staff is planning on parading through the towns of Buffalo, Monon, and Reynolds, in hopes to see many of their students. They will begin in Buffalo at 1:00 p.m. and be led by the fire departments through the town. From there we will head to Monon and parade up and down the streets then off to Reynolds. We encourage each of our students, families, and other community members to come outside and wave, hold up posters, send air hugs, scream and shout and show your support. For families that live in the rural area, we encourage you to drive into the closest town and find a parking spot along one of the streets and wave and honk as we go by. It will be "Viking Pride Friday" so wear your NW gear loud and proud.

Please remember everyone must follow social distancing. Staff will not be getting out of the cars and spectators please do not approach anyone in their cars.
text:
Hello NW Families:

The teachers and staff at North White miss their students tremendously. It has been too long since they saw all of your smiling faces. So on Friday the staff is planning on parading through the towns of Buffalo, Monon, and Reynolds, in hopes to see many of their students. They will begin in Buffalo at 1:00 p.m. and be led by the fire departments through the town. From there we will head to Monon and parade up and down the streets then off to Reynolds. We encourage each of our students, families, and other community members to come outside and wave, hold up posters, send air hugs, scream and shout and show your support. For families that live in the rural area, we encourage you to drive into the closest town and find a parking spot along one of the streets and wave and honk as we go by. It will be "Viking Pride Friday" so wear your NW gear loud and proud.

Please remember everyone must follow social distancing. Staff will not be getting out of the cars and spectators please do not approach anyone in their cars.

News & Review
April 2 at 2:59 PM ¬∑

NORTH WHITE RESPONDS ABOUT SCHOOL CLOSING.

As of right now, North White has the plan in place to continue with our eLearning program to provide the best possible education for our students.
We will utilize eLearning Days on Mondays, Tuesdays, Thursdays and Fridays.
We will also continue to use waiver days on Wednesdays.

Our staff has done an outstanding job of acclimating to the online teaching and learning process.
We are using more programs than ever before to find ways to communicate with and help our students.
We are tracking student progress daily and are calling parents and students when issues arise, such as assignments not being done to the expected level or not getting completed.

At this time, we have not spent our time or resources on the graduation issue.
Since this announcement has been made, we will begin discussions on graduation.
Once a decision is made regarding graduation for our seniors, we will notify our North White Community of the plan.

Nick Eccles, Superintendent of North White School Corporation.

REMINDER: Beginning tomorrow, Monday, March 30th:

NORTH WHITE SCHOOL CORPORATION

BREAKFAST & LUNCH INFORMATION

Starting Monday, March 30th, North White students and anyone else in the household ages 18 and under can get both breakfast and lunch for free (Mondays through Fridays).

Our buses will deliver to students on their normal routes and bus stop locations starting at 8:00 am. Please watch for your bus. Once it arrives, go out and pick up your breakfast and lunch meals.

Students who do not ride a bus will be able to pick up their meals at the Buffalo Christian Church, Reynolds Elementary School or North White Elementary School. These locations will be available from 9:00-9:30 am.

For anyone who missed the above opportunities, we will have meals available for pick up at North White Elementary School from 6:00 p.m.-7:00 p.m.

post_text:
From Mr. Van Der Aa, Middle-High School Principal:

North White Families,

Our staff has truly missed all of our students this past week. Every one of our staff members loves their job because of the children we serve. While we greatly miss our students and being in their presence, we do appreciate the enhanced partnership with families to educate our students together. This teamwork is the only way that we have been successful this past week.

I ask that all families check Skyward (contact Todd Shriver at tshriver@nwhite.k12.in.us if you need help logging in or using it) to check the grades of their students. Please contact your student's teacher(s) if there are any missing assignments and please help your student get caught up over the next week so they are ready for our next day of e-learning when we return from Spring Break.

I know many families had plans to travel for Spring Break that have been canceled. While that is very unfortunate, my hope is that families can still relax and students can rejuvenate so they are ready to finish the school year well.
